{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH8BFQWYANB5LzgugixJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. All 3 tests pass, including the new regression test.\n\n**The bug** was in `src/validate.js:7`. The domain part of the regex used `(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]*)*` — the `*` quantifier on the label characters allowed a label to be **empty**, so `..` matched (a dot, zero characters, another dot). This directly contradicts the function's own comment: \"Labels must be NON-EMPTY — consecutive dots are invalid.\"\n\n**The fix** was a one-character change, `*` → `+`, so each label must contain at least one character:\n\n```js\n/^[^\\s@]+@[A-Za-z0-9-]+(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]+)*\\.[A-Za-z]{2,}$/\n```\n\nNow `user@mail..example.com` is rejected while valid addresses like `ada@example.com` still pass. I also added a regression test covering the consecutive-dots case, since the existing suite (as its own note admitted) let this bug ship."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":316,"cache_read_input_tokens":24183,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":316},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f88a6df8-8ae5-4b6e-a1d0-838e1a92e490","uuid":"d5ff6512-1ac7-445a-a7d7-bd9050c96244","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:50:12.185Z","request_id":"req_011CdH8BEKHD5dQvjhXrFX3z"}
